    public class CycloListener
extends JavaBaseListener
    This is a JavaBaseListener (ANTLR4) implementation that calculates Cyclomatic Complexity measurement, according to McCabe's calculations (http://www.literateprogramming.com/mccabe.pdf). The listener counts plus one for: a) Each method; b) Each switch label; c) Each occurence of: "catch", "do", "for", "else if", "if", "throws", "while"; d) Each "return" statement that is not the last command of a method;
